[_Mobula_ is a genus of ray in the family Myliobatidae (eagle rays). Their appearance is similar to that of manta rays, which are in the same family. Species of this genus are often collectively referred to as "flying mobula" or simply "flying rays", due to their propensity for breaching, sometimes in a spectacular manner.

If the species implicated is the devil fish (_Mobula mobular_), this episode is of great concern as it is an endangered species. The total population was estimated at 400 individuals.

For a picture of a jumping mobula go to http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/45/Mobula_breaching.jpg.

A video of the episode can be seen at http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B-ajNdYRZjo.

A map of the affected area can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/2c2P. - Mod.PMB]
